WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.687
<v Jamie>Jamie here — and Tesla just hit a 'symbolic' self-driving milestone, whatever that means, with Elon Musk saying it's a major step towards safe unsupervised self-driving.

00:00:08.687 --> 00:00:19.045
<v Alex>Alex on markets — and the S&P five hundred is down zero point four one percent, not exactly a thrilling day, with the Dow Jones down one point one three percent.

00:00:19.045 --> 00:00:29.069
<v Maya>Maya from tech — and Palantir is having a great day, posting its fastest revenue growth ever, which is pretty impressive, and they're calling out 'AI slop', whatever that means.

00:00:29.069 --> 00:00:32.411
<v Jamie>Right, exactly, because who doesn't love a good AI controversy?

00:00:32.411 --> 00:00:38.425
<v Alex>Well, the Nasdaq is only down zero point one nine percent, so I guess that's a win.

00:00:38.425 --> 00:00:45.442
<v Maya>And Oracle is up four point nine two percent, which is a big move, after they announced their quarterly earnings.

00:00:45.442 --> 00:00:50.120
<v Alex>Oh, just the usual — beats on earnings and revenue, nothing too exciting.

00:00:50.120 --> 00:00:59.810
<v Maya>And Micron has risen up the ranks of the top U.S companies, which is a big deal, and they weren't even in the top one hundred last year.

00:00:59.810 --> 00:01:02.483
<v Jamie>That's a huge jump — what's driving that?

00:01:02.483 --> 00:01:07.495
<v Alex>Well, their fortunes have changed dramatically, mostly due to their recent investments and partnerships.

00:01:07.495 --> 00:01:14.846
<v Maya>And I heard Spirit Airlines just shut down, which is kind of sad, but also not surprising, given their financial struggles.

00:01:14.846 --> 00:01:19.189
<v Jamie>Yeah, I guess you could say they just ran out of runway.

00:01:19.189 --> 00:01:21.194
<v Alex>Oh, great, a aviation pun.

00:01:21.194 --> 00:01:28.545
<v Maya>And GameStop just made a surprise bid for eBay, which is a huge deal, and could potentially change the retail landscape.

00:01:28.545 --> 00:01:31.218
<v Jamie>That's a big move — what's behind it?

00:01:31.218 --> 00:01:37.901
<v Alex>Well, GameStop is trying to expand its business, but it's not clear how they plan to pay for it.

00:01:37.901 --> 00:01:45.586
<v Maya>And the creator of Roomba is back with a new robot companion, which is kind of cool, but also a bit weird.

00:01:45.586 --> 00:01:48.927
<v Jamie>Yeah, because what everyone needs is a robot friend.

00:01:48.927 --> 00:01:54.942
<v Alex>Anyway, the ten-year Treasury yield is up one point five five percent, which is a big move.

00:01:54.942 --> 00:02:01.959
<v Maya>And the dollar index is up zero point two seven percent, which is not too exciting, but still a move.

00:02:01.959 --> 00:02:05.300
<v Jamie>Right, exactly — it's all about the small moves today.

00:02:05.300 --> 00:02:13.319
<v Maya>And I heard the US government is warning of a severe CopyFail bug affecting major versions of Linux, which is kind of scary.

00:02:13.319 --> 00:02:16.661
<v Jamie>Yeah, because who doesn't love a good cyber threat?

00:02:16.661 --> 00:02:20.336
<v Alex>Well, at least it's not a boring day in tech.

00:02:20.336 --> 00:02:25.014
<v Maya>And the Met Gala just happened, and the fashion is insane, as always.

00:02:25.014 --> 00:02:28.355
<v Jamie>Yeah, because who doesn't love a good fashion disaster?

00:02:28.355 --> 00:02:32.365
<v Alex>Anyway, that's all for today — it's been a wild ride.

00:02:32.365 --> 00:02:37.377
<v Maya>And don't forget to check out the Pulitzer Prize winners, which were just announced.

00:02:37.377 --> 00:02:40.384
<v Jamie>Yeah, because who doesn't love a good book?

00:02:40.384 --> 00:02:44.060
<v Alex>Well, that's all for now — thanks for tuning in.

00:02:44.060 --> 00:02:48.069
<v Maya>And we'll be back tomorrow, with more news and more jokes.

00:02:48.069 --> 00:02:52.747
<v Jamie>This show is for entertainment and education only — nothing here is investment advice.
